  "remarks": "Sergey Muzychenko is Deputy Minister of Construction, Housing, and Utilities of the Russian Federation in charge of the Department of Pricing and Resource Support of Construction and the Department of Urban Planning and Architecture. He is in charge of implementing the policy of the Ministry of Construction in the annexed regions of Donetsk, Luhansk, Zaporizhzhia and Kherson. Subsidies from the federal budget of the Russian Government are channelled through the Ministry of Construction in order to strengthen the “redevelopment” of the Ukrainian regions currently under Russian control. In his position as Deputy Minister, Sergey Muzychenko is implementing policies which undermine or threaten the territorial integrity, sovereignty and independence of Ukraine.",
